<span class="d-none" itemprop="commentCount">10</span> 
    <div class="post-layout--right js-post-comments-component">
        <div id="comments-35929248" class="comments js-comments-container bt bc-black-200 mt12 " data-post-id="35929248" data-min-length="15">
            <ul class="comments-list js-comments-list" data-remaining-comments-count="5" data-canpost="false" data-cansee="true" data-comments-unavailable="false" data-addlink-disabled="true">

                        <li id="comment-59589834" class="comment js-comment " data-comment-id="59589834" data-comment-owner-id="-1" data-comment-score="0">
        <div class="js-comment-actions comment-actions">
            <div class="comment-score js-comment-score js-comment-edit-hide">
            </div>
        </div>
        <div class="comment-text  js-comment-text-and-form">
            <div class="comment-body js-comment-edit-hide">
                
                <span class="comment-copy">HI, This is almost what I need , I need to parse the string (with html content) to HTML which I can query from,but I need it in client side for example in jsFiddle , can you please provide example how it can be done in jsFiddle with the HTML I put in the question,for example to add script after the first script ...I need to get some html as string and provide modified html after I modified it with the requirement I put in the question....Thanks!</span>
                
                <div class="d-inline-flex ai-center">
– <span class="comment-user">user4209821</span>
                </div>
                <span class="comment-date" dir="ltr"><a class="comment-link" href="#comment59589834_35929248">
                    <span class="v-visible-sr">Commented</span>
                    <span title="2016-03-13 07:29:39Z, License: CC BY-SA 3.0" class="relativetime-clean">Mar 13, 2016 at 7:29</span>
                </a></span>
            </div>
        </div>
    </li>
